<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFF99F70CFCA86A1EFB55E304" blockId="45.[826,1441,1330,1903]" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFCA86A1EFC70E123" box="[826,945,1331,1352]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
I have not seen any specimens matching the original description and illustration of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFA156A7CFC67E1EF" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFA156A7CFC67E1EF" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">G. bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the following is based only on the original description. 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFBB46AA3FAC6E1C8" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[1062,1287,1422,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFBB46AA3FAC6E1C8" box="[1062,1287,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">Grammia bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFA156AA3FC6CE1AA" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFA156AA3FC6CE1AA" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the more elongate forewing shape, smaller, less robust body, reduced hindwing antemedial and medial spots, and discrete rather than confluent postmedial and subterminal markings distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFC31690AFBF5E257" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[931,1076,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFC31690AFBF5E257" box="[931,1076,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">G. bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFBD4690AFB1CE257" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1094,1245,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFBD4690AFB1CE257" box="[1094,1245,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not known to occur west of the Cascade/Sierra 
<collectingRegion id="49D4F80EFF99F70CFB656968FA8FE230" box="[1271,1358,1605,1627]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">Nevada</collectingRegion>
crest, although both species could occur together in the northern Sierra 
<collectingRegion id="49D4F80EFF99F70CFC6F69AEFB99E2F2" box="[1021,1112,1667,1689]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">Nevada</collectingRegion>
. The small size and overall pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFC2E698CFBE9E2DD" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[956,1064,1697,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFC2E698CFBE9E2DD" box="[956,1064,1697,1718]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
approach 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFB3B698FFAF6E2DD" box="[1193,1335,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fergusoni">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFB3B698FFAF6E2DD" box="[1193,1335,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">G. fergusoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the straight vs. curved postmedial line, lack of hindwing antemedial and medial spots (well developed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFA1569F2FC62E379" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fergusoni">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFA1569F2FC62E379" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">G. fergusoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and hindwing ground colour (pink vs. reddish orange) suggest that these species are not conspecific. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF99F70CFB966817FBACE324" box="[1028,1133,1850,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fergusoni">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF99F70CFB966817FBACE324" box="[1028,1133,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">fergusoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Sierra 
<collectingRegion id="49D4F80EFF99F70CFCA86874FC54E304" box="[826,917,1881,1903]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="45" pageNumber="552">Nevada</collectingRegion>
. See ‘Remarks’ below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFF9AF70FFF026FEBFEC0E79C" blockId="46.[144,759,198,1015]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFF026FEBFEA7E4B0" box="[144,358,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Description: Head</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFEEF6FEBFE0EE4B0" box="[381,463,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Thorax</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE756FEBFD90E4B0" box="[487,593,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Abdomen</emphasis>
– Unknown; although the head, antennae, and markings of the thorax and abdomen are clearly visible in the illustration accompanying the original description, Stretch (1872) notes in the text description that ‘the condition of the body parts of the only specimen I have seen, is such as to preclude an accurate description.’ This calls into question the accuracy of the illustrated specimen. The thorax and abdomen are depicted with the light and dark striped pattern typical of the genus, but no written description is given. The antennae appear thickened, presumably slightly bipectinate. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE126D1BFE2BE620" box="[384,490,566,587]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Forewing</emphasis>
– Wing expanse given as 1.00 inch, which corresponds to a forewing length of about 
<quantity id="4CE89B09FF9AF70FFE9F6D5FFE9CE6E3" box="[269,349,626,648]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
; ground colour blackish brown, fringes, costa, and anal margin yellowish; antemedial band restricted to wedge at costal margin; medial, postmedial, subterminal bands, and postcubital stripe well developed; medial and postmedial confluent at and extending through postcubital stripe; bands dirty yellowish in colour; anal dash absent. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFDFB6C07FD1AE754" box="[617,731,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Hindwing</emphasis>
– Ground colour described as rose, markings black, consisting of three postmedial spots and partial subterminal band; fringes yellowish; ventrally with similar pattern but more yellowish colour overall, hindwing ground colour orange-rose. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFD176CEEFD37E7B3" box="[645,758,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Genitalia:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFF9AF70FFF026B32FF2AE0FB" blockId="46.[144,759,1055,1168]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFF026B32FF2AE05F" box="[144,235,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Biology:</emphasis>
Unknown. 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFE1C6B32FDBEE05F" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[398,639,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE1C6B32FDBEE05F" box="[398,639,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Grammia bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFE956B13FE5DE039" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[263,412,1085,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE956B13FE5DE039" box="[263,412,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFE456B13FDFEE039" baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[471,575,1085,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blakei">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE456B13FDFEE039" box="[471,575,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. blakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and, like these species may fly in spring or early summer. May be diurnal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFF9AF70FFF026B95FE5AE087" blockId="46.[144,758,1208,1260]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFF026B95FEE0E0A6" box="[144,289,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Distribution:</emphasis>
Known only from Mt. Shasta, 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FF9AF70FFD096B95FD00E0A6" box="[667,705,1208,1229]" country="USA" name="Chicago Academy of Sciences" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" type="Museum">CA</collectionCode>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54AB884EFF9AF70FFF026BFAFF00E087" box="[144,193,1239,1260]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="132B2A69FF9AF70FFEA26BFBFE4EE087" box="[304,399,1238,1260]" captionStart="Figures 126–131" captionStartId="87.[164,254,1685,1704]" captionTargetBox="[240,1365,196,1653]" captionTargetId="figure-0@87.[238,1368,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="87" captionText="Figures 126–131. Distribution of examined specimens of Grammia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5444753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5444753/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Fig. 131</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFF9AF70FFF026A3EFECDE123" blockId="46.[144,758,1299,1352]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFF026A3EFE41E142" box="[144,384,1299,1321]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Molecular variation:</emphasis>
No data available, no extant specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFF9AF70FFF026A42FB2CE5F8" blockId="46.[144,759,1391,1903]" lastBlockId="46.[806,1422,198,403]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFF026A42FF3AE1EF" box="[144,251,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Remarks:</emphasis>
Little additional information on 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFD186A42FD37E1EF" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[650,758,1391,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFD186A42FD37E1EF" box="[650,758,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has come to light since Marion Smith remarked that ‘its specific standing must remain in question’ 70 years ago (
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B1DFF9AF70FFE806AE6FE70E18A" author="Smith ME" box="[274,433,1483,1505]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" refId="ref64404" refString="Smith ME. 1938 a. A revision of the genus Apantesis Walker (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). Unpublished Ph. D. thesis. Urbana: University of Illinois." type="book" year="1938">Smith, 1938a</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, the original description and accompanying illustration leave little doubt that 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFE9F6925FEB8E276" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[269,377,1544,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE9F6925FEB8E276" box="[269,377,1544,1565]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from any other species known to occur in northern 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FF9AF70FFE5D690AFE32E257" box="[463,499,1575,1596]" country="USA" name="Chicago Academy of Sciences" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" type="Museum">CA</collectionCode>
and the Pacific Northwest. Earlier authors often associated it with 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFD4E696BFF14E212" baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blakei">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFD4E696BFF14E212" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. blakei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the differences in markings, coloration, habitat, and geographical range preclude conspecific status with that species. The small size, forewing shape, straight postmedial band, and absence of basal and antemedial bands are characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFD0E69F2FF19E378" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFD0E69F2FF19E378" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the loss of hindwing antemedial and medial elements is rare in 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFE5B6831FD9EE35A" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[457,607,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFE5B6831FD9EE35A" box="[457,607,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly males. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFEB06817FE76E324" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[290,439,1850,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFEB06817FE76E324" box="[290,439,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not known to occur west of the Great Basin ranges and the east slope of the Sierra 
<collectingRegion id="49D4F80EFF9AF70FFCE56FEBFC10E4B7" box="[887,977,198,220]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Nevada</collectingRegion>
, with the nearest records from Sierra Co., 
<collectionCode id="ED01AE29FF9AF70FFCF06FC8FC49E491" box="[866,904,229,250]" country="USA" name="Chicago Academy of Sciences" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" type="Museum">CA</collectionCode>
, about 
<quantity id="4CE89B09FF9AF70FFC7C6FC9FB83E491" box="[1006,1090,228,250]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" unit="km" value="250.0">250 km</quantity>
south-east of Mt. Shasta. Given the phenotypic and biogeographical differences, 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFCB46E0FFC7BE55C" baseAuthorityName="Stretch" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[806,954,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolanderi">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFCB46E0FFC7BE55C" box="[806,954,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. bolanderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFB926E0FFB5AE55C" baseAuthorityName="Dodge" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1024,1179,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsii">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFB926E0FFB5AE55C" box="[1024,1179,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">G. williamsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not conspecific. Until specimens from the vicinity of the 
<typeStatus id="54AB884EFF9AF70FFA926E6CFAF0E53D" box="[1280,1329,321,342]" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">type</typeStatus>
locality are discovered, the taxonomic affinities of this enigmatic 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFF9AF70FFCE26E53FC1FE5F8" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1866" box="[880,990,382,403]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFF9AF70FFCE26E53FC1FE5F8" box="[880,990,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="553">Grammia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will remain uncertain.
</paragraph>
